    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-12-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="24"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d24">
                <head>No. 24.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Tree</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-12-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 3, 1886</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 66.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose a copy of a letter from Capt. J. F.
                    Burke, commanding the Gate City Guard, of Atlanta, Ga.</p>
                <p>This volunteer organization, which is highly commended by his excellency the
                    governor of Georgia, is one of the foremost in the country for drill and
                    discipline.</p>
                <p>As you will see by the inclosure it is the deeire of the organization which is
                    about visiting Europe to wear their uniforms and to carry their arms when on
                    parade.</p>
                <pb facs="0120" n="26" xml:id="pg_26"/>
                <p>Please obtain early information whether the Government to which you are
                    accredited will give the necessary permission, and under what, if any,
                    conditions, and apprise me so that I can notify Governor Gordon in season.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
